# Coding Conventions


## Linter

- **Tool**: eslint
- **Config**: `eslint.config.mjs`

> Follow the linter configuration. Do not disable rules without justification.




## Company Quality Standards

- **QUA-001** (high): All new code must include corresponding tests.
- **QUA-002** (high): Follow the existing code style and conventions of the project.
- **QUA-003** (medium): Functions should do one thing. Keep functions under 50 lines where possible.
- **QUA-004** (medium): Use meaningful variable and function names. Avoid single-letter names except in short lambdas.
- **QUA-005** (medium): Handle errors explicitly. Never swallow exceptions silently.
- **QUA-006** (low): Remove dead code, unused imports, and commented-out code before merging.

## Rules

1. Follow existing naming conventions — consistency over personal preference
2. Match the file naming pattern used throughout the project
3. Run the linter and formatter before committing




